Hi Mougli 

This is what we&#39;re doing at it&#39;s giving us only one html report.

    &lt;target name=&quot;test&quot; depends=&quot;testdirectories&quot; 
		description=&quot;Test with JUnit&quot; &gt;
        &lt;junit fork=&quot;on&quot; dir=&quot;${build}&quot; showoutput=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
            &lt;classpath refid=&quot;testlibs&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;classpath path=&quot;${build.testclasses}&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;classpath path=&quot;${project.jar}&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;classpath path=&quot;${resources.jar}&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;formatter type=&quot;xml&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;jvmarg line=&quot;-Xmx256m -Xss8192k&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;sysproperty key=&quot;user.dir&quot; value=&quot;${testrun}&quot;/&gt;

		&lt;batchtest fork=&quot;yes&quot;&gt;
                &lt;fileset dir=&quot;${tests}&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;include name=&quot;**/*Test.java&quot;/&gt;
                &lt;/fileset&gt;
            &lt;/batchtest&gt;

        &lt;/junit&gt;
    &lt;/target&gt;

    &lt;target name=&quot;report&quot; depends=&quot;test&quot;
        description=&quot;Transform test results from xml to html&quot;&gt;

        &lt;!-- Create directories --&gt;
        &lt;mkdir dir=&quot;${reports.dir}&quot;/&gt;

        &lt;!-- Move the XML output to report directory --&gt;
        &lt;move todir=&quot;${reports.dir}&quot;&gt;
            &lt;fileset dir=&quot;.&quot;&gt;
                &lt;include name=&quot;TEST-*.xml&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;/fileset&gt;
        &lt;/move&gt;

        &lt;junitreport todir=&quot;${reports.dir}&quot;&gt;
            &lt;fileset dir=&quot;${reports.dir}&quot;&gt;
                &lt;include name=&quot;TEST-*.xml&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;/fileset&gt;
            &lt;report format=&quot;noframes&quot; todir=&quot;${reports.dir}&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;/junitreport&gt;
    &lt;/target&gt;

Hope it kan help you.

